// Use this Function node in n8n to avoid "\n" in output
// The trick: wrap HTML in backticks with no indentation or line breaks

return [{
  to: $json.recipientEmail, // pass recipient email to next node
  subject: `Application for ${$json.jobTitle} – Job ID ${$json.jobId}`,
  htmlBody: `<div style="font-family:Segoe UI,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px;color:#1a1a1a;line-height:1.6"><p>Hi ${$json.recipientName},</p><p>Good morning!</p><p>I came across the <strong>${$json.jobTitle}</strong> position (Job ID: <strong>${$json.jobId}</strong>) on your portal and I’m very interested in exploring this opportunity. As a <strong>${$json.yourStatus}</strong> with strong experience in .NET and enterprise application development, I believe my background aligns well with the role.</p><p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br><a href="${$json.jdLink}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View Job Posting</a></p><p><strong>My Profiles:</strong><br>LinkedIn: <a href="${$json.yourLinkedIn}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">${$json.yourLinkedIn}</a><br>Portfolio: <a href="${$json.yourPortfolio}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">${$json.yourPortfolio}</a></p><p>Even if this role isn’t the best fit right now, I’d be glad to stay in touch and explore future opportunities with your team.</p><p>Thank you for your time and consideration. I look forward to your response.</p><p>Best regards,<br><strong>${$json.yourName}</strong><br><span style="color:#555">${$json.yourTagline}</span><br><a href="${$json.yourLinkedIn}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a> • <a href="${$json.yourPortfolio}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Portfolio</a></p></div>`
}];
